<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Kaharz...

You can easily do the Tormented Vah Shir skulls solo.. that's easy enough

Amulet of Sunrays - Scarlett Desert - Burning Priest... You *can* do this solo but it will be difficult. I would recommend having either a druid, necro, or melee partner.

Thought Horror Brain - at 58 85% of the Thought Horrors were light blue to me. I would recommend having a melee partner for this (ranger/monk would be optimal) but you can do it with virtually any class as a partner(assuming same level)

Black Flame Charcoal - You'll most likely need a full group of people to kill enough toilers on "toiler hill" (between ruins and lake) in ME.. good news is that ME is a pickup group zone (atleast it is on Fennin Ro)

The turn in fights.. you really only need 2 things here.. A melee and somebody to to crowd control, the hardest fight will be the first one with the 8 skellies who spawn when you kill the courier.

I did all the ingredient camping with a 54 shaman as my partner while i double boxed my cleric and my rogue. Was very easy and simple. I did the turn in fights with a 55 war, 54 shaman, and me.. THAT was an adventure especially on the first fight with the 8 skellies. If your going in with fewer numbers of helpers, damage shields are your friend (for my 8skellie fight we bummed a druid DS from a passing druid(25pt) + shammy DS potion(26pt) + MoR(15pt) + 8th Coldain ring(8pt).. 74pt DS on mobs is VERY handy

Hope that helps

------------------
[URL=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=12024]Panteroo Mcgillakudy[/URL]
